A severe drought has affected 170,560hectares of farmlands in six eastern and northeasternprovinces, Interior Permanent Secretary Pisarn Mulasartsathornsaid.    He told reporters some 178,790 farming families in 45districts in Chaiyaphum, Korat, Phrae, Chainat, Rayong and Tratprovinces were seeking relief water from the government.    The official did not say what crops have been damaged.    Senior Interior Ministry officials said this week the worsethan average drought this year has affected 14 provinces andmay last until early May. REUTER&#3;